3.	 In what situations would SQLite be a better choice than MySQL?
SQLite would be a better choice than MySQL when it comes to small-scale applications.  
Another situation would be when an application being built will only have one or very few users access the database at the same time.  
In summary, SQLite is best for smaller, simpler applications or scenarios that are portable, easy to use, and have minimal setup.

